# Project: <!-- project-name -->

## Source of truth for agent behavior

- Read and follow `AGENTS.md` at repo root before implementing changes.
- Use `dev-docs/requirements.md` for feature intent and acceptance criteria.
- Use `dev-docs/architecture.md` for system contracts and design constraints.
- Use `dev-docs/roadmap.md` for active priorities.
- Use `dev-docs/changelog.md` + `dev-docs/archive/` for historical decisions.
- After completed changes, load the `dev-docs` skill to update documentation.

## Hard guardrails

<!-- List non-negotiable rules. Examples:
- Treat out/ as generated; never patch it manually.
- Fix things at source; never work around symptoms in output.
